title: 2017 Toyota Camry Hybrid official accessories detailed - CarWale
text:
Toyota recently launched the latest iteration of the Camry Hybrid in India. Check out the list of accessories that the carmaker has rolled out for the sedan.
Convenient package
There are different accessory kits which customers can opt for. However, the convenient package looks to be the most essential kit for Camry owners. This includes floor mats, trunk mats and a car cover. Then, to stack up stuff inside neatly you can opt for a luggage storage, cargo net and a sun visor organiser. In addition, there are optional front sun shades and a back sensor.
Chrome package
This one is for buyers who would love to have that extra bling on their car. This includes chrome embellishments on the OVRM covers, side visor and the side mouldings.
Personalised package
There is also is a personalised pack which includes a wooden centre panel, illuminated scuff plates, car cushions, luggage tray and a trunk mat.
Advanced package
For owners who want their Camry to have something more unique, there is a welcome door lamp with 'Camry' being projected. A heads up display unit can also be had as an add-on fitment from a dealership. Prices of all this equipment can be availed at any Toyota dealers across the country.
